In the slow cooker, combine all the ingredients except the tortillas and toppings. Cover and cook on low for 8 hours or on high for 4 hours. Transfer the chicken to a cutting board and shred it using two forks. Return the shredded chicken to the slow cooker and stir to blend. Warm the tortillas in a dry skillet over medium heat and fill them with the chicken mixture. Serve with the toppings.